quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  69,1,"The Inevitable Reality -"
  69,2,"What is the Inevitable Reality?"
  69,3,"And what can make you know what is the Inevitable Reality?"
  69,4,"Thamūd and ʿAad denied the Striking Calamity [i.e., the Resurrection]."
  69,5,"So as for Thamūd, they were destroyed by the overpowering [blast]."
  69,6,"And as for ʿAad, they were destroyed by a screaming,<sup foot_note=197598>1</sup> violent wind",footnotes:197598:1
  69,7,"Which He [i.e., Allāh] imposed upon them for seven nights and eight days in succession, so you would see the people therein fallen as if they were hollow trunks of palm trees."
  69,8,"Then do you see of them any remains?"